edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.fitting

Class GaussianImageObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.fitting.ImageObject
      • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.fitting.GaussianImageObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GaussianImageObject
extends ImageObject
    An ImageObject that fits to a three-dimensional gaussian that is symmetric in x-y and has no covariance between any of the dimensions.
    Author:
    Colin J. Fuller

        public GaussianImageObject(int label,
                   Image mask,
                   Image parent,
                   ParameterDictionary p)
        Creates a GaussianImageObject from the specified masked region in an Image.
        Parameters:
        label - The greylevel of the object in the Image mask.
        mask - The mask of objects in the Image, with a unique greylevel assigned to each object.
        parent - The Image that the object occurs in and that is masked by mask.
        p - The parameters associated with this analysis.
